DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Unlike single-valued menus, multi-valued menus enable  the
       end-user  to  select  one  or  more  items  from  a  menu.
       set_item_value sets the selected value of the item -- TRUE
       (selected) or FALSE (not selected).  set_item_value may be
       used only with multi-valued menus.  To make a menu  multi-
       valued, use set_menu_opts or menu_opts_off to turn off the
       option O_ONEVALUE.  [see

       item_value returns the select value of item,  either  TRUE
       (selected) or FALSE (unselected).

 vvaalluuee
       set_item_value returns one of the following:
       ----------------------------------------------------------------------
       E_OK               -   The routine returned successfully.
       E_SYSTEM_ERROR     -   System error.
       E_REQUEST_DENIED   -   The menu driver could not process the request.

NNoottiicceess
